commit.message:
Properly support revisions in on_commit handlers

Before this commit, making a second revision after a first atomic
revision transaction has successfully committed does not work properly.
Now, making a new atomic revision inside an on_commit handler works as
expected.

Implementation-wise it looks like it was already supposed to work, but
the internal local stack bookkeeping pops the current frame off the
stack just too late when exiting the contexts. This tricked the
bookkeeping into skipping the second revision creation.
Add a long description for pypi.org

commit.message:
Do not declare wheel to be universal

"universal" is only for wheels that are 2+3 single source
compatible. django-reversion is only compatible with Python 3.6+.

See eg. meshy/pythonwheels#11 (source of https://pythonwheels.com/)

commit.message:
Replace force_text with force_str

The former is deprecated in Django 3.0 and has been an alias for force_str
since Django 2.0:
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/releases/3.0/#django-utils-encoding-force-text-and-smart-text

Use of force_text raises deprecation warnings on Django 3.0.
